pageContext.claim: “And you know my poll numbers with Hispanics? Went up 17 points. … Right now it's 50 percent.”
pageContext.analysis: The NBC/Marist poll Trump is referring to, from mid-January, was quite outdated by the time he made these remarks. It was also an outlier at the time. Other polls had Trump garnering much less support from Hispanics. A Washington Post/ABC poll at the time found 18 percent support. A Quinnipiac University poll found 35 percent. Most polls show that a large majority of Hispanics do not approve of Trump.
